Regime → (Homophily → Diversity)

Building upon the dissemination of culture model by Axelrod (1997) we implement a selection-influence model on beliefs with an alternative dependency between the cultural overlap and probability of interaction between two agents. This function lets us vary the strength of homophily with parameter $h$, to affect the proability of interaction $p$ as a function of cultural overlap $x_{ij}$ like so:

$$p= \begin{cases} (\frac{1}{2})^{1-h}x^h, & \text{if } x\leq.5\\ 1-(\frac{1}{2})^{1-h}(1-x)^h, & \text{if } x > .5\\ \end{cases}$$

This function looks like:

With this function, we ran the following experiment (ran remotely because of computationally expensive simulation):

#!/usr/bin/env python

import defSim as ds
import time

exp = ds.Experiment(seed=269,
                    influence_function="axelrod",
                    attributes_initializer="random_categorical",
                    attribute_parameters={"num_features": [5],
                                          "num_traits": [15]},
                    influence_parameters={"homophily": [.25, .5, 1, 2, 4]},     # .125 & 8 were ran stand-alone 
                    topology="grid",
                    stop_condition="strict_convergence",
                    max_iterations=9999999,
                    network_parameters={"neighborhood": "moore",
                                        "num_agents": 100},
                    communication_regime=["one-to-one", "one-to-many"],
                    output_realizations=["AverageDistance", "Homogeneity", "Regions", "Isolates", 
                                         "SuccessfullInfluence", "Ticks"],
                    repetitions=200)

start = time.time()
my_results = exp.run(parallel=True)
end = time.time()
print("Simulation completed in", round(end - start), "seconds")
my_results.to_csv('AxelrodWithHomophily.csv', index=False)

Clustering → opinion fragmentation

Parameters:

  • confidence_level = [0.1, 0.2]
In [3]:
def simulation_run(N=120,
                   K=10,
                   rewiring=0,
                   confidence_level=0.2,
                   max_ticks=10000,
                   seed_run=random.randint(10000,99999),
                   record_opinions=False):
    random.seed(seed_run)

    G = ds.generate_network("watts_strogatz_graph", n=N, k=K, p=rewiring)
    ds.initialize_attributes(G, realization="random_continuous", num_features=1)
    calculator = ds.dissimilarity_calculator.select_calculator("euclidean")
    calculator.calculate_dissimilarity_networkwide(G)

    iterator = 0
    if record_opinions: opinions_exp1 = []

    while iterator < max_ticks:
        agent_i = ds.focal_agent_sim.select_focal_agent(G,"random")
        agent_j = ds.neighbor_selector_sim.select_neighbors(G,"random",agent_i,"one-to-many")

        ds.influence_sim.spread_influence(G, "bounded_confidence", agent_i, agent_j, "one-to-many",
                                          calculator, convergence_rate=0.5, confidence_level=confidence_level)
        if record_opinions: opinions_exp1.append(list(nx.get_node_attributes(G,'f01').values()))
        iterator += 1
        if not any([True for x in nx.get_edge_attributes(G,'dist').values() if 0.01 < x < confidence_level]):
            break

    if record_opinions: 
        return(opinions_exp1)
    else:
        list_of_clusters = ds.ClusterFinder.create_output(G,cluster_dissimilarity_threshold=confidence_level)
        return(dict(
            seed = seed_run,
            N = N,
            K = K,
            rewiring = rewiring,
            confidence_level = confidence_level,
            ticks = iterator,
            number_of_subgroups = len(list_of_clusters),
            size_biggest_subgroup = list_of_clusters[0],
            transitivity=nx.transitivity(G)
        ))

Simulation experiment¶

In [23]:
def simulation_experiment(personalization=[0.1,0.2,0.3],rewiring_iter=[0,.175,.35],repetitions=3):
    random.seed(123)
    lod = []
    for i,j in itertools.product(personalization,rewiring_iter):
        for x in range(repetitions):
            rundict = dict(personalization=i,
                           rewiring_iter=j)
            rundict.update(simulation_run(rewiring=j,confidence_level=i,max_ticks=10,seed_run=random.randint(10000,99999)))
            lod.append(rundict)
    return(lod)
In [24]:
output = simulation_experiment(repetitions=100)
df = pd.DataFrame(output)
